```wget https://github.com/soulfly07/test/raw/main/satori/1_docker_satori_install.sh && chmod +x 1_docker_satori_install.sh && ./1_docker_satori_install.sh```
```wget https://github.com/soulfly07/test/raw/main/satori/2_satori_install.sh && chmod +x 2_satori_install.sh && ./1_docker_satori_install.sh```
лог - ```ournalctl -fu satori.service```


автостарт  sudo systemctl enable satori.service
запуск   sudo systemctl start satori.service
остановить   sudo systemctl stop satori.service
перезапуск   sudo systemctl restart satori.service
убрать автостарт  sudo systemctl disable satori.service

If you want to limit the resource usage of Satori, you can do so using Docker. Here is an example that uses no more than half of the CPUs on your machine and sets a memory limit to 512 MB:
$docker update --cpus=".5" --memory="512m" satorineuron
This command will ensure that Satori runs with the specified resource constraints.
